					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>Two kabbalistic works of Samuel Portaleone.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="143r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Tiḳune Zohar</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש תקוני הזהר</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/30828161">Portaleone, Samuel ben Elisha</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/30828161">שער אריה, שמואל בן אלישע</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The manuscript begins with the commentaries on Tiḳunim 56 to 70 (folios 1r-119r) and continues with the commentaries on Tiḳunim 1 to 11 (folios 120r-143r).</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">יהי שם ה' מבורך שזיכנו להשלים מה שיעדנו לעשות היום יו' ז' ניסן <date calendar="Seleucid">ש'פ'ג'</date> שהוא ז' אפרילו <name type="place">ס' מרטינו</name> אשר תחת ממשלת המרקיסו קרלו דאיסטי יר"ח. <locus n="143r"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="143r" to="159v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Taḳanat ha-shavim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תקנת השבים</title>
							<author>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/30828161" xml:lang="en">Portaleone, Samuel ben Elisha</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/30828161">שער אריה, שמואל בן אלישע</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Incomplete at the end.</p>
								<p>Folio 143v contains a piece commenting upon the 13 midot.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>159 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>180/200</height>
										<width>95/145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>159 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end). </p>
									<p>Original Hebrew foliation.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 16 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Defective at the end.</p>
									<p>Water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="33 42" writtenLines="33 42">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Running headings.</p>
									<p>Additions and comments in the margin.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian cursive script of the 17th century. Apparently an autograph of <name type="person" role="scribe">Samuel ben Elisha Portaleone</name>.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Front and back flyleaves come from a printed edition of Seder ha-hafṭarot.</p>
							<p>Folio 143v contains notes of the former owners, including an entry of birth dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1684</date>, and some astrological calculations.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Modern binding, hard-board cover with ivory leather spine.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Perush Tikkune Haz-Zohar, Etc. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,090.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
