							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Giuseppe Almanzi</name> (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 196: his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for £1,000 through <name type="org">Asher &amp; Co.</name>, Berlin dealer to the British Museum (see <ref target="Paisey_1997" type="page">131-153</ref>): inscribed, folio [160v] (fse001v).</p>
						</acquisition>
